Myblog on CodeIgniter execution instructions.

Myblog on Codeigniter uses MYSQL therefore the database must be build.

1) Build database:

Once MYSQL is installed.

By default this configuration for the database is used:

$db['default']['hostname'] = "localhost";
$db['default']['username'] = "root";
$db['default']['password'] = '123456';
$db['default']['database'] = 'myblog';
$db['default']['dbdriver'] = 'mysql';

Configuration can be changed in the CodeIgniter file application/config/database.php

The database schema is in the myblog.sql file in the root directory of the app.
This database has some example data.

2) Install Apache + Modules for execute PHP

3) Copy this folder to the apache directory.

Visit locahost
